    "A spatial location, for example, [7, 8], would refer to the seventh row and eighth column of the 2D data matrix (Figure 3).",
    "A series of values such as [7, 8, 0], [7, 8, 1] and [7, 8, 2] … [7, 8, 99] would determine values of pixel location [7, 8] at bands (0, 1, 2 … 99) of a hyperspectral data cube with 100 bands.",
    "Such consecutive values form the spectrum or spectral signature from a series of voxels (ElMasry and Nakauchi, 2016).",
    "There are three conventional specifications of the imaging systems to generate a hyperspectral data cube.",
    "First specification includes whisk broom imaging which captures a single pixel in all specified spectral channels at an instance (Figure 4A)."
